{
  "texts": [
    "The recursive definition of hypergradient h(T) i needs to be unrolled all the way back to initial parameters (0).",
    "The key takeaway from Eq.",
    "(61) is that training hypergradients affect the model parameters throughout all of training.",
    "By assuming a convex model and loss, Koh and Liang's (2017) simplified formulation ignores this very real effect.",
    "As Chen et al. (2021) observe, hypergradients often cause non-convex models to converge to a vastly different risk minimizer."
  ]
}